  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: There is no spinner when signing in to existing account. Sign in button can be clicked multiple times. User may not understand that she is being signed in. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nAfter clicking the sign in button there is an info (and spinner) that I'm being signed in. I understand what is happening.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nNo spinner. User can interact with the screen (can edit inputs, press sign in multiple times, etc.)\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Install Status\r\n- Open the app\r\n- Go to add existing account\r\n- Provide passphrase and password. Then click sign in button \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, March 1 (new onboarding screens, #3326)\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
